  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mid-infrared broadband absorber of full semiconductor epi-layers</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-04-25</subfield>
    <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">6</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We demonstrate mid-infrared dual channel near-perfect absorbers based on full semiconductor epi-layers theoretically. Strong absorption (>99.9%) is observed at 25.04 THz. Through introducing composite grating and controlling the thickness of the dielectric layer, we can get a broadband absorption with absorptivity above 80% at the range from <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>8</mn><mtext> μm</mtext></math> to <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>12</mn><mtext> μm</mtext></math> with a good incidence angle tolerance. The structure investigated in this paper shows a broadband, all-semiconductor, plasmonic architecture, which is of great importance for many applications such as bolometers, cloaking, imaging devices and also can be used in enhancing interaction of mid-infrared radiation with integrated semiconductor optoelectronic elements.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
